<P>
   IMPEACH-ASSESS _ Since his days as an undergraduate, Bill
Clinton has believed, his oldest friends say, that he could talk
his way out of any predicament. From then until now, he has usually
been right. Suddenly, whether last week in Washington or this week
in the Middle East, Clinton has turned pensive, wan and remote. BY
R.W. Apple Jr.
</P>
