<SLUG> BC-NY-IMPEACH-RALLY-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WIESEL, MORRISON, DOCTOROW AT ANTI-IMPEACHMENT RALLY 
</HEADLINE>
  (rl) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Artists, scholars and politicians, including Elie
Wiesel, Toni Morrison and Gloria Steinem, criticized the
impeachment proceedings as a hypocritical sham at a rally on Monday
night at New York University.
</P>
<P>
   ``Who shall judge the judges?'' asked Wiesel.
</P>
<P>
   About 700 people jammed an auditorium and an overflow room at
the rally. Organizers included NYU law professor Stephen Holmes and
the historian Sean Wilentz; both testified last week on behalf of
Clinton before the House Judiciary Committee.
</P>
<P>
   Rep. Jerrold Nadler, D-N.Y., along with the actor Alec Baldwin,
urged audience members to lobby representatives to vote against
impeachment.
</P>
<P>
   E.L. Doctorow, the novelist, said the impeachment proceedings
had ``all the legitimacy of a coup d'etat.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I can't think of an American president that hasn't lied to the
American people,'' he added. ``Perhaps the problem with Clinton is
that his lie is without grandeur.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-12-15-98 0102EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
