<HEADLINE>
SMITH CONFIDENT HE'LL PLAY SUNDAY 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By TIM TYERS  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   TEMPE, Ariz. - Defensive tackle  &UR; Mark Smith plans to play Sunday
against the New Orleans Saints, although it will be a surprise to
Coach &UR; Vince Tobin.
</P>
<P>
   ``My ankle is getting better with treatment every day,'' said
Smith, who ditched the crutches he was using last week. ``I hope to
test it in practice on Friday and then play on Sunday.''
</P>
<P>
   Tobin, however, sounded less optimistic when asked about the
availability of Smith, middle linebacker  &UR; Ron McKinnon (strained
knee) and cornerback  &UR; Tommy Knight (hamstring connector) for
Sunday's game.
</P>
<P>
   ``They would probably be listed in the questionable to doubtful
range,'' Tobin said. ``I'll have to see how they are on Wednesday
and Thursday. There has to be significant improvement to be where I
think they will be healthy enough to help us, but stranger things
have happened.
</P>
<P>
   ``I know they want to play, badly. If they're physically able,
they will certainly do their best to be there.''
</P>
<P>
   Offensive guard/tackle  &UR; Matt Joyce, who has been sidelined for a
month after having a broken knuckle joint surgically repaired, said
he will be able to play with the aid of a cast. Receiver/returner
 &UR; Eric Metcalf sprained an ankle Sunday but is expected to play. &QL; 
Missing middle &QL; 
With Smith, defensive tackle  &UR; Eric Swann and McKinnon sidelined and
McKinnon's backup,  &UR; Mark Maddox, playing on an injured knee, the
Cards were vulnerable to the run up the middle, and the Eagles took
advantage in the first half before defensive coordinator  &UR; Dave
McGinnis went to a five-man defensive front.
</P>
<P>
   But a quick fix doesn't prohibit the Saints from trying to
exploit the same weakness. The injuries eventually forced the
Cardinals to play undersized  &UR; Terry Irving at middle linebacker.
</P>
<P>
   ```We've had the five-man package all year on and off, and it
has helped us on occasion,'' Tobin said. ``It's like anything, when
you do the same thing all the time, people will find ways to attack
it. It kind of changed the flow of the game and they went away from
some of the things that we were having problems with in the first
half and tried to throw the ball.
</P>
<P>
   ``But as far as the overall solution, there is no overall
solution other than the guys who are playing there have got to play
better and more consistent in order to play the run. We hope to
solidify that area and make them go elsewhere.'' &QL; 
Extra points &QL; 
It was pointed out to Tobin that two Cardinals wins and two losses
by suddenly struggling Dallas would make the Cards NFC East champs.
His response: ``I don't get too excited about things we can't
control. All we need to do is control where we are. All we need to
think about is beating New Orleans.''
</P>
<P>
   The win at Philadelphia was Arizona's first December road win
since 1993; the Cards' 4-4 road record is the best since 1984; and
their 4-4 NFC East record is their best since 1994. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-12-15-98 0110EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
