<P>
   FBN-VECSEY-COLUMN (Undated) _ Sports of The Times column the NFL
vagabonds _ the owners who keep moving their teams. By George
Vecsey.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-NBA-RACE (New York) _ The negotiations have often been
heated, with both sides pointing fingers and hurling profanity.
Egos have been bruised, and enormous amounts of money and pride
have been sacrificed. But while it sounds like any other labor war
in America, one dynamic separates the National Basketball
Association from other disputes _ the issue of race. The players
union is 85 percent black and has begun to question whether it is
being treated with respect by an ownership that is 100 percent
white. Any number of players have already concluded they are not
being taken seriously and seem angry enough to sacrifice a season
to prove a point. By Selena Roberts and Mike Wise.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-PATRIOTS-STADIUM (Hartford, Conn.) _ Misgivings remain, and
the deal is still the most generous ever offered to the owner of a
National Football League team, but today the Connecticut
Legislature will vote to build a $375 million stadium and commit up
to $1.5 billion over the next 30 years to support the New England
Patriots. By Mike Allen.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-NFL-REPLAYS (Undated) _ Commissioner Tagliabue, George Young
and the NFL's competition committee talk over the replay issue and
decide whether to bring it to a vote by the owners. By Mike
Freeman.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-MEETINGS (Nashville) _ Latest baseball news as the winter
meeting draws to a close. The focus is on the backlash among
baseball executives to the way negotiations are currently being
conducted, with everyone in the dark but the agents. By Buster
Olney.
</P>
<P>
   For information and repeats call the News Service at (888)
346-9867 or (212) 556-1927. And be sure to look for other sports
stories from our partners: Bloomberg News, The Boston Globe, Cox
News Service, Hearst News Service, The Arizona Republic, Kansas
City Star, Fort Worth Star-Telegram, Los Angeles Daily News, San
Francisco Chronicle and Seattle Post-Intelligencer.
