u l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-GETAWAY-FESTIVALS16-C     12-15 0741
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GETAWAY-FESTIVALS16-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Southern Happenings
 &HT;    By Paula Crouch Thrasher
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  Augusta, Ga. _ ``Haunter of Ruins,'' an exhibition of 65
photographs by Clarence John Laughlin, is featured at the Morris
Museum of Art through Jan. 17. 706-724-7501.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Madison, Ga. _ ``Hurricane Relief Open House,'' a special tour
of eight ``little houses'' in the town known for its mansions, will
be held Saturday. The event, benefiting hurricane victims in
Central America and the Caribbean, will feature cabins, cottages,
an orangerie and a former chicken house, all decorated for the
holidays. Minimum $10 donation. 706-342-4787.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Pine Mountain, Ga. _ Fantasy in Lights, Callaway Gardens'
ride-through light and sound holiday celebration, highlighted by a
Nativity pageant of lights on the beach. Through Dec. 27.
1-800-225-5292.
</P>
<P>
