<HEADLINE>
HOW DO I HELP GET ROGER MARIS INTO THE HALL OF FAME?
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: Where can I write to help get Roger Maris into the Baseball
Hall of Fame? I think it is disgraceful that this has never been
done.
</P>
<P>
   _ J.P., Arlington, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: The group to contact is the Veterans' Committee of the
National Baseball Hall of Fame, which will announce its next
selections in March 1999.
</P>
<P>
   The 15-member committee includes former players, club
executives, broadcasters and sportswriters:
</P>
<P>
   Players: Yogi Berra, Juan Marichal, Stan Musial, Pee Wee Reese
and Ted Williams.
</P>
<P>
   Executives: Buzzie Bavasi, Joe L. Brown, Buck O'Neil, Hank
Peters and Bill White.
</P>
<P>
   Media: Bob Broeg, Ken Coleman, Jerome Holtzman, Len Koppett and
Al Lewis.
</P>
<P>
   Letters can be sent to individual committee members in care of
the Veterans' Committee, National Baseball Hall of Fame, Box 590,
Cooperstown, NY 13326.
</P>
<P>
   The Hall of Fame will forward only letters addressed to a
specific committee member, so you must send 15 separate letters to
reach the entire group.
</P>
<P>
   Q: What schools are leaving the Western Athletic Conference?
</P>
<P>
   _ M.E., via the Internet
</P>
<P>
   A: The following schools will form the new Mountain West
Conference on July 1, 1999: Air Force, Brigham Young, Colorado
State, New Mexico, San Diego State, University of Nevada-Las Vegas,
Utah and Wyoming.
</P>
<P>
   The new name became necessary when the NCAA ruled that the
departing schools could not take it with them. They also may lose
$2.6 million in basketball-tournament revenue.
</P>
<P>
   The schools remaining in the WAC are Fresno State, Hawaii, Rice,
San Jose State, SMU, TCU, University of Texas-El Paso and Tulsa.
</P>
<P>
   The split is an ``acrimonious, bitter divorce,'' Utah basketball
coach Rick Majerus told a San Jose Mercury News sportswriter in
October.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I write to Regis and Kathie Lee?
</P>
<P>
   _ A.L., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: Send letters in care of the show to ``LIVE! With Regis &AMP;
Kathie Lee,'' 7 Lincoln Square, Fifth Floor, New York, NY 10023.
</P>
<P>
   To request tickets for the show, send a self-addressed stamped
envelope to ``LIVE!'' tickets, Box 777, Ansonia Station, New York,
NY 10023-0777.
</P>
<P>
   There's a limit of four tickets per request, which may take
several months to fulfill. The show also has a special address for
entries to its daily trivia contest. Send these on postcards to
``LIVE!'' Trivia Contest, Box 108, Ansonia Station, New York, NY
10023.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
