<P>
   CLINTON-PASTOR-1216 _ JERUSALEM _ As Bill Clinton descended from
Air Force One in Israel last weekend, his face lit up and he gave a
big televised Arkansas hug to the Rev. John Anthony, a Jerusalem
pastor who went to kindergarten with the American president.
Anthony's using his moment of fame , mostly in Israeli media, to
tell Americans to forgive their president at this crucial time.
Anthony says he is sure that Clinton's trip Tuesday to Bethlehem
Church of the Nativity included quiet time and prayer, which the
first lady Hillary Rodham Clinton has told him is their sustenance.
Developing. (Kaplow, Cox News Service).
