<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR WEDNESDAY, DECEMBER 16
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Wednesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-HIGGINBOTHAM-NYT (moved on Monday, Dec. 14)
</P>
<P>
   The obituary of Judge A. Leon Higginbotham Jr. moved by the New
York Times News Service on Monday, Dec. 14, yesterday referred
incorrectly in some editions to the date and source of his
appointment to the Federal District Court in Philadelphia. He was
named in September 1963, not 1964. While nominated by President
John F. Kennedy, he was sworn in the next year during the
Administration of President Lyndon B. Johnson.
</P>
<P>
   BC-REGULATING-DERIVATIVES-NYT (moved on Monday, Dec. 14.)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, Dec. 14,
about the outlook for tighter market regulation after the
near-collapse of Long-Term Capital Management misidentified the
employer of Thomas Clark, a managing director in derivative
securities who attributed Long-Term's problem to its heavy
borrowing. Mr. Clark works for Morgan Stanley Dean Witter &AMP;
Company, not for J.P. Morgan. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
