A1570 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBN-REPLAY-BOS &LR;      12-15 0349
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-REPLAY-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NO RETURN TO REPLAY THIS SEASON, NFL DECIDES 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By WILL MCDONOUGH  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Instant replay will not be used to help NFL officials in the
playoffs this season.
</P>
<P>
   By a 7-1 vote, the Competition Committee Tuesday rejected a
proposal by commissioner Paul Tagliabue to use instant replay to
help the beleaguered officials in postseason play.
</P>
<P>
   ``I spoke with the committee (before the vote) and outlined the
pros and cons of it after speaking with all of the clubs across the
league,'' said Tagliabue. ``Everyone on the (conference) call
recognized the advantages to using it in a given game to have the
(officiating) crew look at replay, but they were against making the
change for postseason.
</P>
<P>
   ``Jerry Jones (the Dallas owner) was for it, but the rest were
against it, even though they voted, 6-2, in favor of having some
kind of instant replay for regular-season and postseason games in
1999.''
</P>
<P>
   So there will be no replay this season.
</P>
<P>
   But Tagliabue said most involved want the system back for the
start of the 1999 season.
</P>
<P>
   ``What we have to do now,'' he said, ``is put together a system
that most all teams will be in favor of.''
</P>
<P>
   According to Tagliabue, the people on the conference call agreed
that the Competition Committee should come up with a system that it
will highly endorse to all the teams at the annual NFL meeting in
Phoenix next March.
</P>
<P>
   ``I pointed out to the members of the committee that with the
new technology on television, it is becoming more and more
difficult to officiate these games,'' said Tagliabue. ``I pointed
out to them that the greatest players in the game make mistakes
each week and officials are going to make mistakes each week. Our
officating is good. We have just had some bad calls on some
high-profile plays recently.
</P>
<P>
   ``Jim Tunney (former game official) told me last week that the
expectations for officials in our league are just too high. What I
hope we can do is use the technology now available to help in the
future.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-12-15-98 2058EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
