<P>
   BKN-NBA-RACE (New York) _ The negotiations have often been
heated, with both sides pointing fingers and hurling profanity.
Egos have been bruised, and enormous amounts of money and pride
have been sacrificed. But while it sounds like any other labor war
in America, one dynamic separates the National Basketball
Association from other disputes _ the issue of race. The players
union is 85 percent black and has begun to question whether it is
being treated with respect by an ownership that is 100 percent
white. Any number of players have already concluded they are not
being taken seriously and seem angry enough to sacrifice a season
to prove a point. By Selena Roberts and Mike Wise.
