   (NYT5) SCARSDALE, N.Y. -- Dec. 15, 1998 -- WINE-TALK, 12-15 --
Oversize bottles like the one lifted by Meghin Casey at Zachy's
make striking gifts. If you want to be electrifying in your
gift-giving, buy a big bottle, and I mean really big. A six-liter
bottle is the equivalent of eight regular 750-milliliter bottles,
and often it can be an excellent value. (G. Paul Burnett/New York
Times Photo)
