impeachment of President Clinton. The House is expected to cast
their historic vote on Thursday. (Stephen Crowley/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) WASHINGTON -- Dec. 15, 1998 -- IMPEACH, 12-15 -- In order
for members of the House of Representatives to vote on a topic
pending before the legislative body, each member inserts their
identification card into the reader at right and presses the
appropriate button. The system, used in all voting by the Congress,
will be used to cast Thursday's historic vote on the impeachment of
President Clinton. (Stephen Crowley/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) BETHLEHEM -- Dec. 15, 1998 -- MIDEAST-CLINTON, 12-15 --
Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat salutes as President Clinton
arrives in Bethlehem on Tuesday. Clinton arrived in the West Bank
city following a three-way meeting between himself, Arafat and
Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu which failed to reach
agreements on further Israeli withdrawals. (Rina Castelnuovo/New
York Times Photo) *LITE
</P>
